channel.title: Interleaved RSS Feed
channel.description: This is an interleaved feed of the most recent entries from each RSS source, skipping any feeds with errors.

item.title: Role Reversal: DOJ Comes to Donald Trump's Defense (Sort Of)
Biden’s Charlottesville moment? POTUS torched for telling DNC anti-Israel mob outside ‘has a point’
item.description: President Biden raised eyebrows Monday night when he appeared to make a similar characterization about anti-Israel protesters to one he has pinned on Donald Trump regarding neo-Nazis in Charlottesville, Virginia.

item.title: Professor: Biden-Harris Regulations Drain Families
item.description: Biden-Harris administration regulations are on pace to cost the average American family $47,000, according to a University of Chicago economics professor.

item.title: JD Vance Tears Into Andy Beshear Over 'Disgusting' Rape Comment About Family
Biden speech delayed until after primetime
item.description: President Biden's keynote speech at the Democratic National Convention didn't start until after primetime and wrapped well after midnight on the East Coast.

item.title: James Taylor's DNC Performance Scrapped Due to Scheduling Issues
item.description: James Taylor's scheduled performance on the first day of the 2024 Democratic National Convention in Chicago was scrapped due to scheduling issues, which also led to President Joe Biden's speech being moved out of primetime, according to reports.

item.title: Disney's Woke Star Wars Show 'The Acolyte' Crashes, Burns, and Gets Canceled After Just One Season
Benjamin Harrison won the White House by receiving the electoral majority, but losing the popular vote
item.description: Benjamin Harrison served as the 23rd President of the United States. He defeated incumbent Grover Cleveland in 1888, but lost to the Democrat in 1892.

item.title: US Wants Treaty to Limit Plastic
item.description: The United States has announced it will lend its backing to a global treaty limiting the amount of plastics that are produced worldwide, signaling a policy shift from previous resistance on such efforts, according to Reuters.

item.title: NEW: Jake Tapper's Response to Nancy Pelosi's Cutthroat Remarks About Biden Was Something Else
Democratic delegates approve platform with mistake mentioning Biden's second term
item.description: Delegates at the Democratic National Convention voted on Monday to approve a written party platform that repeatedly affirms President Biden as the party's presidential nominee.

item.title: Trump Repeats: Will Accept 'Fair' Election Results
item.description: Former President Donald Trump again said he will accept the results of the upcoming election if it's "fair and free."

item.title: They're So Bad at This: Democrat Attack on JD Vance's Background During DNC Widely Misses the Mark
Former teacher reveals which students suffered 'the most' under Walz's pandemic-era guidelines
item.description: A former Minnesota teacher told Fox News Digital that rules enforced by Gov. Tim Walz during the coronavirus pandemic poorly impacted immigrant students.

item.title: Trump Defends Harris Slams: She's Not 'Very Good'
item.description: Republican presidential nominee Donald Trump is defending the personal attacks he has made against rival Democrat Vice President Kamala Harris, but also said slams might be necessary to win back the White House.
